"""
Test 2 — Linear Motion Validation  (FIXED v5)
==============================================

ROOT CAUSE (confirmed)
-----------------------
  Right motor is physically installed in reverse direction.
  To compensate, the wiring uses IN3=LOW/IN4=HIGH for forward
  instead of IN3=HIGH/IN4=LOW.

  This means when we try to SLOW the right motor for steering,
  we must ADD to ENB duty cycle (not subtract), because the motor
  logic is inverted on that side.

  v5 fixes this with a dedicated _apply_steering() method that
  knows the right motor is physically reversed.

FIXES IN v5
-----------
  FIX-M4  Steering correction inverted for right motor.
          Gyro Z rate used directly (no EKF lag).
          Robot curves right → gz negative → increase right PWM
          (because right motor is reversed, more PWM = more braking)

  FIX-M5  Time-matched return — backward leg runs for exactly
          the same duration as the forward leg.

  FIX-M3  LiDAR forward angle = 180° (LiDAR faces backward).

TUNING
------
  GYRO_STEER_KP = 8.0   works for most setups
  Increase to 12.0 if still curving
  Decrease to 4.0 if robot oscillates/wobbles

Usage:
  python3 test2_v5.py
  python3 test2_v5.py --kp 12.0
  python3 test2_v5.py --kp 4.0
"""

